title.narrative: Consensus Building On Rule Of Law

description.narrative: This project is about building consensus among Law Ministers from 54 member countries of the Commonwealth on global rule of law issues such as access to justice, the Sustainable Development Goals, countering terrorism and violent extremism, tackling cybercrime, combating corruption, money laundering and the financing of terrorism, international peace and security. Agreed outcomes from Law Ministers Meetings provide common policy positions for the Meeting of Commonwealth Heads of Government (CHOGM), and advocacy at relevant international fora. The Commonwealth Law Bulletin contributes to a wider communication of Law Ministers’ discussions and helps disseminate legal information throughout the Commonwealth.
